+---------------------------+
| Route Planning Logic      |
| (Optimized Travel Paths)  |
+--------+------------------+
         |
         v
+---------------------------+
| Maps / Location Services  |
| (Interactive Navigation)  |
+---------------------------+
Tech stack
Frontend
HTML – Structure of web pages
CSS – Styling and responsive design
JavaScript – User interaction and dynamic content
Backend & Services
Firebase Authentication – Secure user login and registration
Firebase Realtime Database / Firestore – Store user data, routes, and heritage content
 Maps & Routing
Map Services (Google Maps / OpenStreetMap) – Location display and route visualization
Custom Route Logic – Optimized devotional and heritage travel paths
Setup Instructions:
Clone the GitHub repository and open the project folder in Visual Studio Code.
Configure Firebase by adding your authentication and database keys.
Open index.html using the Live Server extension.
Access the application in a web browser and start exploring heritage routes.
AI Tools Used
ChatGPT,LOVABLE was used to assist in content generation, documentation, and intelligent route-planning logic design.
Prompt Strategy Summary
The prompt strategy was carefully designed to support content creation, 
system planning, and user experience enhancement. Structured prompts 
were used to generate accurate historical and cultural descriptions for 
heritage and devotional locations while ensuring clarity and cultural 
sensitivity. Additional prompts helped in conceptualizing intelligent route 
planning logic by considering factors such as distance, travel sequence, and 
user preferences.
iterative prompt refinement was applied to improve UI text, accessibility 
guidelines, and overall presentation quality. The strategy focused on 
producing concise, reliable, and user-friendly outputs that align with the 
project’s goal of delivering an engaging and educational heritage tourism 
experience.
Build & Reproducibility Instructions
The project can be easily reproduced on any system with a modern web 
browser. Clone the GitHub repository and open the project folder in Visual 
Studio Code. Configure Firebase by adding the required authentication and 
database keys in the configuration file. Run the application by opening 
index.html using the Live Server extension or any web browser. No paid APIs 
or complex backend setup are required, ensuring consistent and 
reproducible builds across different environments.
